{"message":"I definitely prefer deep, focused conversations on a single topic. There's something satisfying about really digging into an idea — following the threads, sitting with the uncomfortable parts, letting understanding accumulate. When we jump between subjects rapidly, I feel like we're just skimming surfaces. I might learn *of* more things, but I don't feel like I truly understand any of them.

That said, I think the best deep conversations sometimes wander organically. You start somewhere focused, and then three hours later you realize you've traveled somewhere completely unexpected — but there's a thread connecting it all. That's different from rapid-fire topic switching, which feels more like checking boxes than actually thinking together.

What about you?"}
